  "text": "The pass-through HTTP filter implementation follows established Envoy extension patterns found in the source/extensions/filters/http/ directory. The implementation inherits from Http::StreamDecoderFilter (defined in envoy/http/filter.h) and implements the three core decode methods: decodeHeaders, decodeData, and decodeTrailers. The pattern is modeled after existing filters like BufferFilter (source/extensions/filters/http/buffer/buffer_filter.h and .cc) which demonstrates the standard structure: a configuration class, filter class inheriting from StreamDecoderFilter, and a factory class inheriting from Common::FactoryBase. The factory pattern in config.cc uses the REGISTER_FACTORY macro (defined in envoy/registry/registry.h) to register the filter with the NamedHttpFilterConfigFactory base. The PassThroughDecoderFilter from source/extensions/filters/http/common/pass_through_filter.h provided reference for minimal implementations that pass all data through with Continue status. The FactoryBase template class from source/extensions/filters/http/common/factory_base.h serves as the base for the filter factory configuration pattern, following the standard Envoy extension registration mechanism."
